    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Rings of glass added to the undersides of glass vessels after their bodies have been made.  They are usually flattened so that their edges extend beyond the bottom of the vessels.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000021271/Newman, Illustrated Dictionary of Glass (1977)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Ringen van glas die toegevoegd worden aan de onderzijden van reeds vervaardigde glazen vaten. Zij worden meestal plat gedrukt zodat hun randen uitsteken buiten de bodems van de vaten.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>在玻璃器皿瓶身製作完畢後附加於其底部的玻璃環。這些底環通常會壓平，使其邊緣向外延展，超出器皿底部。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
